ENTRY            A0369   20260127   20260327   20260327       A130
SUBENT        A0369001   20260127   20260327   20260327       A130
BIB                 10         31
TITLE      Projectile fragmentation of 112Sn at E/Lab=1*A GeV
AUTHOR     (A.Stolz, T.Faestermann, J.Friese, P.Kienle,
           H.-J.Koerner, M.Miinch, R.Schneider, E.Wefers,
           K.Zeitelhack, K.Suemmerer, H.Geissel, J.Geri,
           G.Muenzenberg, C.Schlegel, R.S.Simon, H.Weick,
           M.Hellstroem, M.N.Mineva, P.Thirolf)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,65,064603,2002)
INSTITUTE  (2GERMUN,2GERGSI,2SWDLND,2GERLMU)
FACILITY   (SYNCH,2GERGSI) The experiment was performed at the
           fragment separator facility.
SAMPLE     4007 mg/cm2 beryllium target in front of the
           fragment separator. With a total nuclear reaction
           cross section the total reaction probability of the
           primary beam in this target was 45%.
DETECTOR   (IOCH) The chamber had an active area of 200 x 360
           mm2 and a drift length of 10 mm in the direction of
           the beam. The chamber was operated with CF4 gas at
           atmospheric pressure.
           (SCIN) For the measurement of the time of flight,
           2-mm-thick plastic scintillators (BC-420) were mounted
           at the two focal planes of the FRS.
METHOD     (TOF) The length of the flight path between the
           scintillators was 35 m.
             Two independent measurements of the time of
           flight were used to achieve a mass resolution of
           delta-A = 0.32 (FWHM).
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
HISTORY    (20020624C)
           (20021217U) Last checking has been done.
           (20260125A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
           ERR-T -> DATA-ERR.
ENDBIB              31
COMMON               1          3
EN
MEV/A
         1.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           38
